{
    "elem.1.36": {
        "id": "elem.1.36",
        "n": 36,
        "type": "proposition",
        "enunciation": "Parallelograms which are on equal bases and in the same parallels are equal to one another.",
        "proof": [
            {
                "text": "Let `ABCD`, `EFGH` be parallelograms which are on equal bases `BC`, `FG` and in the same parallels `AH`, `BG`;  I say that the parallelogram `ABCD` is equal to `EFGH`.",
                "refs": [],
                "emphs": [
                    "ABCD",
                    "EFGH",
                    "BC",
                    "FG",
                    "AH",
                    "BG",
                    "ABCD",
                    "EFGH"
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For let `BE`, `CH` be joined.",
                "refs": [],
                "emphs": [
                    "BE",
                    "CH"
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Then, since `BC` is equal to `FG` while `FG` is equal to `EH`, > `BC` is also equal to `EH`. [elem.1.c.n.1]",
                "refs": [],
                "emphs": [
                    "BC",
                    "FG",
                    "FG",
                    "EH"
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But they are also parallel.",
                "refs": [],
                "emphs": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And `EB`, `HC` join them; but straight lines joining equal and parallel straight lines (at the extremities which are) in the same directions (respectively) are equal and parallel. [elem.1.33]",
                "refs": [
                    "elem.1.33"
                ],
                "emphs": [
                    "EB",
                    "HC"
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore `EBCH` is a parallelogram. [elem.1.34]",
                "refs": [
                    "elem.1.34"
                ],
                "emphs": [
                    "EBCH"
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And it is equal to `ABCD`; for it has the same base `BC` with it, and is in the same parallels `BC`, `AH` with it. [elem.1.35]",
                "refs": [
                    "elem.1.35"
                ],
                "emphs": [
                    "ABCD",
                    "BC",
                    "BC",
                    "AH"
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For the same reason also `EFGH` is equal to the same `EBCH`; [elem.1.35] so that the parallelogram `ABCD` is also equal to `EFGH`. [elem.1.c.n.1]",
                "refs": [
                    "elem.1.35",
                    "elem.1.c.n.1"
                ],
                "emphs": [
                    "EFGH",
                    "EBCH",
                    "ABCD",
                    "EFGH"
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore etc. Q. E. D.",
                "refs": [],
                "emphs": []
            }
        ]
    }
}